# belarusian sky culture name
msgid "Belarusian"
msgstr "Bielorruso"

# belarusian sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"Astronomy constellations found in Belarus, a country in Eastern Europe bordered\n"
"by Russia to the northeast, Ukraine to the south, Poland to the west, and\n"
"Lithuania and Latvia to the northwest."
msgstr ""
"Constelaciones de astronomía encontradas en Bielorrusia, un país en Europa "
"del Este bordeado por Rusia al noreste, Ucrania al sur, Polonia al oeste y "
"Lituania y Letonia al noroeste."

# belarusian sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"Belarus is landlocked and contains large tracts of marshy land and thousands of\n"
"lakes. Forests cover about 40% of the country. Belarus is exceptional in that\n"
"people in the villages have preserved their traditional knowledge about the\n"
"stars and related beliefs, right through to the present time. The illustrations\n"
"are by no means exhaustive. In fact, many asterisms have multiple recorded\n"
"meanings, ranging from ancient to Christianized."
msgstr ""
"Bielorrusia no tiene salida al mar y contiene grandes extensiones de tierra "
"pantanosa y miles de lagos. Los bosques cubren alrededor del 40% del país. "
"Bielorrusia es excepcional porque la gente de las aldeas ha conservado sus "
"conocimientos tradicionales sobre las estrellas y las creencias "
"relacionadas, hasta la actualidad. Las ilustraciones no son exhaustivas. De "
"hecho, muchos asterismos tienen múltiples significados registrados, que van "
"desde la antigüedad hasta la cristianización."

